          "feature_type": "TEXT_FEATURE_MUST_KNOW",
          "value": {
            "localized_texts": [
              {
                "language_code": "en",
                "text": "Terms & Conditions: Valid Foreign Visitors (Non-Malaysian Citizens) Booking confirmation must be presented at the cashier counter Physical tickets must be redeemed at the cashier counter All guests are required to comply with the rules and regulations displayed at Space & Time Cube as a condition of entry. Children aged 3 and below enter for Free of charge Child tickets are only valid for children under 13 years old and must be accompanied by a guardian at all times. Guests aged 13 and above are required to purchase an adult ticket. Senior citizens aged 60 and above, as well as individuals with disabilities, are eligible to purchase tickets at RM38. MyKad or a disability card is required to present at the Cashier counter for verification. Outside food and drinks are not permitted within Space & Time Cube premises. For your convenience, complimentary locker facilities are available for safe storage. Tickets are not valid with other discounts, promotions, privileges, or loyalty programs Tickets are not exchangeable for cash. Lost or damaged tickets will not be replaced or accepted Expired tickets will not be accepted, and strictly no extensions are allowed In the event of a private function or special event to changes operating hours, we will provide advance notice via our social media channels at least one day prior. Space & Time Cube Malaysia reserves the right to amend the T&Cs without prior notice"
              }
            ]
